properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 25 at 6:24AM PST until January 25 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Areas of Dense Fog this Morning...

.Areas of dense fog have developed over portions of the Valley.
Motorists in the area should be prepared for sudden changes in
visibility and longer travel times due to reduced visibility.
Conditions are expected to improve later this morning.

* WHAT...Areas of visibility below one quarter mile in dense fog.

* WHERE...Southern Sacramento Valley County.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Roads impacted include, but not limited to,
Interstate 80, Highway 50, Highway 99 and Interstate 5.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING
